title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1982-02-16
lineage: MAC (modified Nakamichi CM-700 mics > Sony TC-D5M on Maxell metal tape, about 20 feet in front of the soundboard) > Nak Dragon playback > Cardas audiophile cables > HHB CDR 800 master CD > Samsung SW-232B extraction (EAC v0.9 beta
description: Shakedown Street-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil-> Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O-> Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Might As Well China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Black Peter-> Playin' In The Band-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
Warfield I never had the pleasure of going to the Warfield thoes tickets were hard to get whish I had been there. 
This is a great 80s show, the sound quality is decent but not great. 
Worth a listen for sure but it is not soundboard quality.

dolby here ,too bummer,man. upon further listening this here rather sweet puppy of a recording gives me the sense of doctoring ,also. an awsome off the master recording doesn't need someone messing with dolby-it is not listed as having any dolby input while rolling at the show or during playback but my ears yearn to hear a little of the last bit of ringing out of the cymbals - I'll deal with that tiny tiny bit of analogue hiss any day for that crisp live sound.
Not a bad show at all, if overly full of cowboy songs, but this is the best out of three tapes and it's hard to hear the band for the audience.
